projects.name: Bitcoin Hyper
projects.desc: Bitcoin Hyper is a low-cap Layer 2 and DeFi solution for Bitcoin, aiming to bring scalable decentralized finance infrastructure to the Bitcoin ecosystem. It is currently in presale and targets institutional demand for BTC-based DeFi, offering innovative scaling and interoperability features.

projects.name: Vault AI
projects.desc: Vault AI merges artificial intelligence with DeFi tools on its own native blockchain, aiming to provide advanced financial products and analytics. Its focus is on leveraging AI for smarter DeFi strategies and risk management, targeting both retail and institutional users. The project is in presale and has not yet reached mainstream adoption.

projects.name: Qubetics
projects.desc: Qubetics is a blockchain platform focused on tokenizing real-world assets such as real estate and intellectual property. It has raised $14.5M in its $TICS token presale and aims to make asset ownership more accessible and liquid through blockchain-based fractionalization.

projects.name: Web3Bay
projects.desc: Web3Bay is an e-commerce platform that offers users a 5% discount on purchases when using its native 3BAY token. It aims to disrupt online retail by integrating blockchain-based rewards and payment systems, but is still in early-stage presale.

projects.name: Cogni AI
projects.desc: Cogni AI is a blockchain project allocating 50% of its tokens to presale, focusing on natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) applications. It aims to provide decentralized AI services and tools for developers and enterprises.

projects.name: Lightchain AI
projects.desc: Lightchain AI introduces a 'Proof of Intelligence' consensus mechanism and reserves 40% of its tokens for early investors. The project is designed to integrate AI directly into blockchain consensus and validation, aiming for a more efficient and intelligent network.

projects.name: Solaxy
projects.desc: Solaxy is a Layer-2 scaling solution for Solana, designed to improve scalability and transaction throughput. It has secured $22M in funding and has undergone audits, but is still in the early stages of adoption.
